'''Potta Ashram''' is a [[Catholic]] charismatic renewal centre in Potta, [[Thrissur District]] of [[Kerala]]. The centre is managed by the Vincentian Congregation. The centre comes under [[Syro-Malabar Catholic Diocese of Irinjalakuda]].<ref>{{cite web
|url=http://www.churchnewssite.com/portal/?p=9532 
|title=Divine Retreat Centre <U+2013> Kerala 
|publisher=Churchnewssite 
|accessdate=2013-06-06}}</ref><ref>{{cite web
|url=http://www.pottaashram.com/index.php
|title=Home
|publisher=Potta Ashram 
|accessdate=2013-06-06}}</ref>

The Potta Ashram was founded in 1977 as the centre to direct and to co-ordinate popular mission retreats. It functioned as the headquarters and residences of the directors of the Center, Frs. [[George Panackal V.C.]] and  Romulus Nedumchalil, etc., who used to conduct mission retreats and visitations from here.<ref>http://www.drcm.org/about-us/overview DRCM</ref>

